
                   ##########################################
                   CONFIGURE Directory for the Tinker Package
                   ##########################################

      This directory contains autoconf configure files provided by
      Christoph Junghans as per the email below. They are untested and
      may need modification or updating for the current Tinker version.

      Hi,

      To make the build a bit easier, I have created two files to build
      Tinker with GNU autotools, just copy Makefile.am and configure.ac
      to the Tinker source directory and run:

      $ autoreconf -i -v
      $ ./configure
      $ make

      Cheers,
      Christoph Junghans

